  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And in so many words, the business became a nonstarter because of the duties imposed.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Because obviously, Austria produced wines as well, so-- the Pinot.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It's like the common market today versus any other economic blocks.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my father, with the help of his older brother, the lawyer, Bela-- Dr., Dr.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Bela Weiler, had excellent connections in town.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And due to information which they received from the town hall and so on, they realized in which direction the town is going to develop.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was always an important trading post, being a border town.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it is a very old city of the Roman times.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And it was-- maybe historically, I should have put that first-- a Roman city called Scarbantia.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I've seen once on a map that first ever Jewish settlements in Europe or even the European part of Russia were in that city.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And Buda-- because Pest was a much later developed twin city of Budapest, now it's called.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because the western Hungary was called Pannonia in the Roman times.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And according to stories, the first Jews came with the Roman armies either as slaves or traders.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I've seen a map-- in fact, it was just by coincidence-- where there were two blue dots showing.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And these were the two cities where the first Jews were known of.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Needless to say that the Hungarians who occupied the country 1,000 years ago were-- and came somewhere in the border of China and Manchuria or Russia, being a nomadic people, were somehow never very Jew-friendly.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But there were Jews living under maybe difficult conditions.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And in our city, I have a book, which was written even by a non-Jew, where they tell the story of the Jews being allowed into the city and trade, first temporarily, then permanently.",
      "word_count": 34
    }
  ],
